\f0\fs24 \cf0 Abstract
\b\fs12 \
\pard\pardeftab709\ri0\sl200\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs14 \cf0 We here present a set of interactive parser-based CALL programs for North S\'e1mi. The programs are based on a finite state morphological analyser and  a constraint grammar parser which is used for syntactic analysis and navigating in the dialogues. The analysers provide effective and reliable handling of a wide variety of user input. In addition, relaxation of the grammatical analysis of the user input enables locating grammatical errors and reacting to the errors with appropriate feedback messages. \
}

